# .claude/ holds ~30 git worktrees (full monorepo checkouts each). Without this,
# un-ignoring a service pulls in every worktree's copy of it → snapshot balloons
# to tens of MB → `railway up` /up upload times out. MUST stay ignored.
.claude/
pytest-of-muaza/
test-results/
# Service directories are intentionally NOT excluded — the per-service toggle was
# RETIRED 2026-06-14. Deploys stay clean now without flipping any lines:
#   * Railway `watchPatterns` scope GitHub builds: each service rebuilds only when
#     its OWN dir changes (rag-api -> adil-rag-api/**, landing -> adil-landing/**,
#     doc-worker -> adil-document-uploader/**). A push to one can't break another
#     (that was the 2026-06-12 chat-backend outage).
#   * adil-frontend-next deploys from its own subdir (rootDirectory unset) — it
#     never does a repo-root upload at all.
# A repo-root CLI deploy (document-uploader / report-bridge via their deploy.sh)
# now includes every service's source — kept small by the universal excludes above
# (node_modules/.next/.venv/.claude worktrees) — and each finds its own files.
scripts/
tests/
